The heavily pregnant wife of a man shot dead by an intruder at his home in Sunshine, Melbourne saw the gunman before he escaped.

The 43-year-old man was killed on Tuesday morning while his wife and young son were at their home in Allison Street, Sunshine, and the  gunman is still on the loose, the Herald Sun reported.

It is believed the victim confronted an intruder in the early hours of Tuesday morning when he was shot. It is not yet known if it was a random or targetted attack.

