Police were called to the home about 5.30am where they found the body of the man, who was badly injured and could not be revived.

His wife was seen collapsing in the street and other family members broke down at the scene as others tried to comfort them.

Police including members of the Dog Unit have begun searching the area for the gunman but say no one has been arrested.

The victim's family members, including his young son, were at home at the time of the shooting, 3AW reported.

But police have yet to confirm the circumstances surrounding the shooting, with homicide detectives expected to arrive at the scene to investigate.

Police are interviewing the victim's family members and neighbours.

